class RelationshipInModel

RelationshipInModel 1 -- 1 ModelRelationship
A ModelRelationship has A RelationshipInModel. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one RelationshipInModel.
A RelationshipInModel has A ModelRelationship. It must always have exactly, one, and can never have none. And there is an upper bound of at most one ModelRelationship.
There must always be an equal number of ModelRelationship and RelationshipInModel, connected as Pairs. When a RelationshipInModel is created, its ModelRelationship must be created at the same time. When a RelationshipInModel is deleted, its ModelRelationship is deleted at the same time.
